The paper explores the origins of network paradoxes in online social networks, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses mathematical properties of networks, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the behavioral origins of the paradoxes, which could place it in the cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) sub-category. The paper also discusses the correlation between degree and attribute, which could place it in the cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses statistical properties of sampling, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
